President Barack Obama made the case that higher temperatures lead to increases in wildfires, which send allergy-causing particulates into the air that can lead to greater and more serious incidents of asthma .
'Well you know Malia had asthma when she was four, and because we had good health insurance, we were able to knock it out early,' the president said .
Obama said the health scare resulted in a single trip to the emergency room for his daughter Malia - who at the age of 16 now lives a full and active life, inhaler free .